2018年3月，马斯克宣布该公司调整了计划，将优先考虑行人和骑自行车的人<ref>{{Cite web|title=Adjusting The Boring Company plan: all tunnels & Hyperloop will prioritize pedestrians & cyclists over cars|url=https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/972233079342297088|accessdate=2018-03-10|author=Musk|date=2018-03-09|first=Elon|work=@elonmusk|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310171620/https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/972233079342297088|archivedate=2018-03-10}}</ref>；只有在满足所有其他“个性化公共交通需求”之后，才会考虑运送汽车。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Will still transport cars, but only after all personalized mass transit needs are met. It's a matter of courtesy & fairness. If someone can't afford a car, they should go first.|url=https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/972235526848708608|accessdate=2018-03-10|author=Musk|date=2018-03-09|first=Elon|work=@elonmusk|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310174206/https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/972235526848708608|archivedate=2018-03-10}}</ref>

在2018年初，无聊公司从SpaceX分拆出来，成为一个独立的[[法人團體|公司实体]]。早期员工的[[股東權益|权益]]不到10％，伊隆·马斯克所持有的则超过90％。由于SpaceX股东的不满，无聊公司于2018年12月把6％的股权分配给SpaceX。<ref name="wsj20181217">{{Cite news|author=Copeland|first=Rob|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-new-boring-co-faced-questions-over-spacex-financial-ties-11545078371|title=Elon Musk's New Boring Co. Faced Questions Over SpaceX Financial Ties|work=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]]|date=2018-12-17|accessdate=2018-12-18|quote=''When the Boring Co. was earlier this year spun into its own firm, more than 90% of the equity went to Mr. Musk and the rest to early employees, ... The Boring Co. has since given some equity to SpaceX as compensation for the help, ... about 6% of Boring stock, “based on the value of land, time and other resources contributed since creation of the company,” ''|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218044810/https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-new-boring-co-faced-questions-over-spacex-financial-ties-11545078371|archivedate=2018-12-18}}</ref>

2018年12月，无聊公司向公众展示了位于霍桑的一英里（1.6公里）长的测试隧道。<ref name="musk20181218">{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nSIzsMlwMUY|title=The Boring Company Event Webcast|date=2018-12-18|medium=video|publisher=The Boring Company|accessdate=2018-12-22|archive-date=2018-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224022116/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nSIzsMlwMUY|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2018年，无聊公司从内部筹集了1.13亿美元。<ref name="bloomberg20190725">[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-25/elon-musk-s-boring-co-raises-120-million-in-first-outside-investment Elon Musk’s Boring Co. Raises $120 Million in First Outside Investment. This is on top of the $113 million the startup brought in last year.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818162205/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-25/elon-musk-s-boring-co-raises-120-million-in-first-outside-investment|date=August 18, 2019}}, Bloomberg News, 25 July 2019, accessed 18 August 2019.</ref>2019年7月，无聊公司获得了第一笔外部投资，向多家风险投资公司出售了价值1.2亿美元的股票。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Khalid|first=Amrita|title=Elon Musk's Boring Co. raises $120 million in outside funding|url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/07/25/elon-musk-raises-120-million-boring-co/|work=Engadget|date=2019-06-26|language=en|accessdate=2019-07-26|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726034350/https://www.engadget.com/2019/07/25/elon-musk-raises-120-million-boring-co/|archivedate=2019-07-26}}</ref> 

2019年11月，史蒂夫·戴维斯（Steve Davis）成为无聊公司的总裁。戴维斯2003年加入SpaceX，是其最早的雇员之一，他拥有粒子物理学和航空航天工程双硕士学位。在管理SpaceX华盛顿特区办公室同时，他还在[[喬治梅森大學|乔治梅森大学]]攻读经济学博士学位。他2010年时撰写了有关美元贬值的论文，他还开设了一家酒吧，“成为华盛顿最早接受[[比特币|比特币]]的餐厅之一”。<ref name="bloomberg2019115">{{Cite news|author=McBride|first=Sarahd|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-15/elon-musk-s-boring-co-is-run-by-a-former-bar-owner-who-can-quote-ayn-rand|title=Elon Musk's Boring Co. Is Run by a Former Bar Owner Who Can Quote Ayn Rand|work=[[Bloomberg_News|Bloomberg News]]|date=2019-11-15|accessdate=2019-12-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210045125/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-15/elon-musk-s-boring-co-is-run-by-a-former-bar-owner-who-can-quote-ayn-rand|archivedate=2019-12-10}}</ref>

